notes.test structure: This test does not use any contextual terms identified by the scanner
notes.valid_description: These use real NHTSA-recognized WMI codes and have correctly calculated check digits at position 9
notes.invalid_description: These are invalid due to: wrong check digits, invalid characters (I, O, Q), incorrect length, or fake WMI codes
notes.check_digit_info: The check digit is calculated using weighted position values and modulo 11. If result is 10, check digit is 'X'
notes.wmi_info: WMI (World Manufacturer Identifier) codes in valid VINs are from real manufacturers.
